The increase in COVID-19 deaths in the Western Cape is putting pressure on cemeteries across Cape Town, particularly for Muslim burials. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The increase in COVID-19 deaths in the Western Cape is putting pressure on cemeteries across Cape Town, particularly for Muslim burials. The local community has been outraged this week, over extra charges levied for late burials in one of its private cemeteries. READ: Eastern Cape families unwrap corpses to perform rituals The City of Cape Town says it's trying to create extra burial space, particularly for Muslim graves. It can currently only accommodate 150 Muslim burials a month. eNCA reporter, Lindsay Dentlinger shares more details in the video above.